title: Charles Dickens 200th Anniversary Collection Vol. 3
creator: Charles Dickens
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox Charles Dickens 200th Anniversary Collection Vol. 3 The Charles Dickens 200th Anniversary Collection comprises short works previously unrecorded for LibriVox - fiction, essays, poetry, letters, magazine articles and speeches - and each volume will be a pot pourri of all genres and periods of his writing. The first volume was released on Dickens' 200th birthday, February 7th 2012. Further volumes will follow during the anniversary year. This is the third volume, and includes fiction, letters, magazine articles, poetry, a chapter from Pictures of Italy and a couple of good Dickens rants. For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobook; short stories; poetry; essays; letters
